                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#65r">Fol. 65r</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 65r: ዛቲ፡ ማጽሐፍ፡ ዘተስፋ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ኃደስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ ሙከዕ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written over a previous donation note in the same hand that added the name of Täsfa Mikaʾel to supplication formulas. It states that Täsfa Mikaʾel donated the Ms. to the church and ends with an excommunication against those who stole the book or erased its text.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#74va">Fols. 74va-75</locus>rb: Maḫbärä mǝʾmänan "Congregation of the Faithful" or Mälkǝʿa qwǝrban, incomplete. <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 74r: ማህበረ፡ ምዕመናን፡ ወምእመናት፡ እለ፡ ኪያከ፡ ተአመኑ፡ ለነሲአ፡ ሥጋከ፡ ወትረ፡ ኀበ፡ ተአየኑ። ወልደ፡ አብ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ እንዘ፡ ኢይትፈለጥ፡ እምሕፅኑ። እስብክሎሙ፡ ሕማመከ፡ ወመስቀለከ፡ እዜኑ። ጸጋ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሊተ፡ እምሰማይ፡ ፈኑ። …</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Cp. A. DILLMANN, Chrestomathia Aethiopica, Lipsiae 1866 [repr. in E. HARMMERSCHMIDT, Anthologia Aethiopica, Hildesheim – Zürich – New York 1988], 131-136.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-signs, indicating the place where the omitted passage, written in the upper margin belong: fols. 2rb, 61rb, 63ra, 64vb, 66rb, 69va.&#xD;
- Omitted letters and words written interlineally: e.g., fols. 68rb, 71vab, 73ra.&#xD;
- Rubrication not executed on fols. 70v-73v (hand b).&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of the donor(s) are left unfilled (hand b): fols. e.g., fols. 66va, 67vb, 68rb.&#xD;
- Illegible note in pencil on fol. 75v.&#xD;
- Fols. 76 and 77 (quire B) are a fragment of an older Ms. inserted in the codex sideways; they contain ʿarke-hymns addressing different saints.</item>
                     </list>
